# 5. Name the command that determines the state of the SSH service.

# First need to update apt packages
# Then need to upgrade installed apt packages
# Then need to install the SSH server. After it's running we can run "sudo service ssh status" to see the SSH service state.

# sudo apt -y update
# sudo apt -y upgrade
# sudo apt-get -y install openssh-server
# to start the service: service ssh start
# restart/stop
sudo service ssh status